comment.author: 45586426@N06
comment._content: A3D-2 Skywarrior captured making a violent rocket assisted take off. (JATO/RATO) Code ZB of VAH-4 'Fourrunners' on tail with zigzag marking. Large Modex side number 2 with squadron emblem directly behind. From another aspect, a picture of the same aircraft during the same take off as in the 'flickr' pic: a3skywarriorforwhidbey.org/138912_vah-4_jato.jpg Full Navy Bureau serial number 138912 on lower tail, ZB code above with same marking, Modex 2 on nose and squadron emblem directly behind. The aircraft had a short existence. Some notes; A3D-2 Skywarrior 138912 Accepted By US Navy Dec 1956 Salvaged and scrapped after accident aboard USS Oriskany while operated by VAH-2. Reference to the incident from this dedicated 'A-3 Skywarrior Association' web page: www.a3skywarrior.com/memorial/full_accident_date.htm VAH 4. Det F. CVA 14. USS Oriskany A3D-2 Bu No 138912. 8/20/1960. (20 August 1960) Lost an engine during take off from NAS Cubi Point and the A/C hit the water. It is not known exactly what the outcome was for the four named crew members.

comment.author: 45586426@N06
comment._content:
Many thanks for the kind supply of modified picture internet link.

Unfortunately the A-3 Skywarrior accident link has also been modified and thus a further search is necessary to re-establish a link to that relevant webpage......

The internet is a constantly evolving and ephemeral transient phenomena .
Several links provided by me in some 1500 detailed comments to 'Flickr' military aviation images have over a period of over just two years changed or been deleted and lost.
Especially the A-3 Skywarrior Association and A-4 Skyhawk Association internet website links and those links to their webpages as they have both rebuilt them.

Hope my comment was helpful and informative and also thank the San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive for displaying the image.
